<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <main class="shell">
    <section class="top">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">External API</p>
        <h1>Weather Fetch Dashboard</h1>
      </div>
      <form id="weatherForm">
        <select id="city">
          <option>Delhi</option>
          <option>Mumbai</option>
          <option>Bengaluru</option>
          <option>Kolkata</option>
        </select>
        <button>Fetch Weather</button>
      </form>
    </section>
    <section id="weatherCard" class="weather-card">Choose a city and fetch live weather.</section>
    <section class="oauth">
      <h2>OAuth Concept</h2>
      <p>OAuth lets a user grant limited access to an app without sharing their password. A typical flow redirects the user to a provider, receives an authorization code, exchanges it for an access token, and uses that token when calling protected APIs.</p>
      <p>This demo uses Open-Meteo because it needs no API key, but the server-side route is where an OAuth access token would normally be attached.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
